-- Franklin Templeton Investments Appoints Adam Quaife as Director
-- B y   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 2012-07-17T06:29:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/franklin-templeton-investments-appoints-adam-quaife-as-director.html
Franklin Resources Inc. (BEN) , the manager
of the Franklin and Templeton mutual funds, appointed Adam Quaife as senior director for central and eastern Europe and the
Middle East for  Franklin Templeton  Investments.  Quaife, who joined Franklin Templeton’s institutional
business in 2002, will be based in Dubai and report to Vivek
Kudva, Franklin Templeton Investments’ managing director for
India and CEEMEA, according to an e-mailed statement from Dubai.
His appointment is effective August 1.  Quaife replaces Andrew Ashton, who will be relocating to
San Mateo, California in early August to take up a newly-created
role as head of the firm’s international consultant and research
group, the company said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Arif Sharif in Dubai at 
